Students must complete an academic thesis on a topic of their choice that demonstrates both knowledge and application of the basic analytical and methodological skills involved with studying International Relations or one of the regions (e.g. EU, post-Soviet space, Baltic Sea Region). The thesis defence procedure is Pursuant to the Guidelines for submission and defending of the final thesis, adopted by the Johan Skytte Institute of Political Studies.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The general goals of a thesis are to investigate an issue or problem concerning the field of international relations in depth, to collect original empirical material or data and to analyse this in the light of the corresponding conceptual or theoretical framework, providing the research results as clear and reasoned conclusions.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completing the MA thesis the student:
- establishes research questions independently and select suitable theoretical treatments and methods for their analysis;
- structures research logically and purposefully;
- independently finds and uses suitable empirical and theoretical sources;
- argues and justifies their standpoints understandably and logically;
- uses terms, data and facts correctly and knows the rules of formalising research work;
- bases their conclusions on analysis and summarises in conformity with the line of thought of the thesis; and
- can explain and defend the results of their research in academic discussion and answer questions related to the research.
